    <entry>
        <title type="html"><![CDATA[New Plugin Release 3.4.5]]></title>
        <id>https://simplejwtlogin.com/releases/simple-jwt-login-release-3.4.5</id>
        <link href="https://simplejwtlogin.com/releases/simple-jwt-login-release-3.4.5"/>
        <updated>2022-04-11T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[Released version 3.4.5]]></summary>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>The version <code>3.4.5</code> has been released today on <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/simple-jwt-login" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">WordPress</a>.</p>
<p>This update introduces two new Autologin features: a redirect on failure and a shortcode for displaying error details.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="new-features">New Features<a href="https://simplejwtlogin.com/releases/simple-jwt-login-release-3.4.5#new-features" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to New Features" title="Direct link to New Features" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li class="">Add Redirect on Fail Autologin</li>
<li class="">Shortcode for displaying Autologin errors</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="redirect-on-fail">Redirect on Fail<a href="https://simplejwtlogin.com/releases/simple-jwt-login-release-3.4.5#redirect-on-fail" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Redirect on Fail" title="Direct link to Redirect on Fail" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>This feature allows you to set a redirect URL for when Autologin fails - for example, when the JWT is invalid or expired - so you can show users a helpful error page instead of a blank screen.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="shortcode-for-autologin-errors">Shortcode for Autologin Errors<a href="https://simplejwtlogin.com/releases/simple-jwt-login-release-3.4.5#shortcode-for-autologin-errors" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Shortcode for Autologin Errors" title="Direct link to Shortcode for Autologin Errors" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>The new shortcode lets you display the autologin error code or message directly on any page:</p>
<div class="language-text codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-text codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">[simple-jwt-login:request key="error_code"]</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<div class="language-text codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-text codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">[simple-jwt-login:request key="error_message"]</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>You can also use it to read any query parameter from the URL. For example, given:</p>
<div class="language-text codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-text codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">https://simplejwtlogin.com?my_parameter=test&amp;error_code=21&amp;error_message=This is an error</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<ul>
<li class=""><code>[simple-jwt-login:request key="error_code"]</code> → <code>21</code></li>
<li class=""><code>[simple-jwt-login:request key="error_message"]</code> → <code>This is an error</code></li>
<li class=""><code>[simple-jwt-login:request key="my_parameter"]</code> → <code>test</code></li>
</ul>
<div class="theme-admonition theme-admonition-note admonition_xJq3 alert alert--secondary"><div class="admonitionHeading_Gvgb"><span class="admonitionIcon_Rf37"><svg viewBox="0 0 14 16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M6.3 5.69a.942.942 0 0 1-.28-.7c0-.28.09-.52.28-.7.19-.18.42-.28.7-.28.28 0 .52.09.7.28.18.19.28.42.28.7 0 .28-.09.52-.28.7a1 1 0 0 1-.7.3c-.28 0-.52-.11-.7-.3zM8 7.99c-.02-.25-.11-.48-.31-.69-.2-.19-.42-.3-.69-.31H6c-.27.02-.48.13-.69.31-.2.2-.3.44-.31.69h1v3c.02.27.11.5.31.69.2.2.42.31.69.31h1c.27 0 .48-.11.69-.31.2-.19.3-.42.31-.69H8V7.98v.01zM7 2.3c-3.14 0-5.7 2.54-5.7 5.68 0 3.14 2.56 5.7 5.7 5.7s5.7-2.55 5.7-5.7c0-3.15-2.56-5.69-5.7-5.69v.01zM7 .98c3.86 0 7 3.14 7 7s-3.14 7-7 7-7-3.12-7-7 3.14-7 7-7z"></path></svg></span>note</div><div class="admonitionContent_BuS1"><p>These shortcodes strip all HTML tags from the output.</p></div></div>
<hr>
<p>If you encounter any issues after updating, please open an <a href="https://github.com/nicumicle/simple-jwt-login/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">issue</a> on GitHub.</p>]]></content>
        <author>
            <name>Nicu Micle</name>
            <uri>https://github.com/nicumicle</uri>
        </author>
