    </entry>
    <entry>
        <title type="html"><![CDATA[New Plugin Release 3.4.4]]></title>
        <id>https://simplejwtlogin.com/releases/simple-jwt-login-release-3.4.4</id>
        <link href="https://simplejwtlogin.com/releases/simple-jwt-login-release-3.4.4"/>
        <updated>2022-04-03T00:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[Released version 3.4.4]]></summary>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>The version <code>3.4.4</code> has been released today on <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/simple-jwt-login" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">WordPress</a>.</p>
<p>This update brings new hooks for customizing responses, a fix for empty JWT headers, and a new OpenAPI spec.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="new-features">New Features<a href="https://simplejwtlogin.com/releases/simple-jwt-login-release-3.4.4#new-features" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to New Features" title="Direct link to New Features" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li class="">New hooks have been added to allow customization of all success responses</li>
<li class="">New <a href="https://github.com/nicumicle/simple-jwt-login/blob/master/postman/openapi.yaml" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">OpenAPI</a> spec file has been added</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="bug-fixes">Bug Fixes<a href="https://simplejwtlogin.com/releases/simple-jwt-login-release-3.4.4#bug-fixes" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Bug Fixes" title="Direct link to Bug Fixes" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<ul>
